    "notes": [
      {
        "category": "summary",
        "text": "An update is available for gegl.\nThis update affects Rocky Linux 8.\nA Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list",
        "title": "Topic"
      },
      {
        "category": "description",
        "text": "GEGL (Generic Graphics Library) is a graph-based image processing framework.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* gimp: GIMP: Arbitrary code execution via heap-based buffer overflow in HDR file parsing (CVE-2026-2050)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n\nThis advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.",
        "title": "Description"
      },
